const faqSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'FAQPage',
  mainEntity: [
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'Do skin gummies actually work?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Clinical evidence supports several ingredients found in skin gummies. A systematic review of 11 randomized controlled trials found that collagen peptide supplementation (2.5-10g daily for 8-12 weeks) significantly improved skin elasticity, hydration, and reduced wrinkle depth compared to placebo. Hyaluronic acid supplementation (120-240mg daily) improved skin moisture in multiple clinical trials. Vitamin C is essential for collagen synthesis — deficiency directly causes skin deterioration (scurvy). Vitamin E provides antioxidant protection against UV-induced skin damage. The key is choosing products with clinically studied ingredients at adequate doses.' },
    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'What is the best vitamin for glowing skin?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Vitamin C is the single most important vitamin for skin health. It is essential for collagen synthesis (the structural protein that gives skin firmness and elasticity), it is a potent antioxidant that neutralizes free radicals from UV exposure and pollution, it inhibits melanin production (reducing hyperpigmentation), and it enhances the effectiveness of sunscreen. Vitamin E works synergistically with vitamin C — together they provide 4x the antioxidant protection of either alone. Vitamin A (retinoids) promotes skin cell turnover. Biotin supports skin cell regeneration. A combination of vitamin C, E, and collagen provides the most comprehensive skin support.' },
    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'How long do skin gummies take to show results?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Skin cells turn over approximately every 28 days, so the minimum timeframe to see results from any skin supplement is 4 weeks. Most clinical trials on collagen and hyaluronic acid show measurable improvements in skin hydration at 4-6 weeks, improvements in elasticity and wrinkle depth at 8-12 weeks, and continued improvement through 24 weeks of consistent use. Antioxidant vitamins (C, E) provide internal protection that builds gradually. Do not expect overnight results — skin health supplements work by supporting the biological processes that maintain and repair skin tissue over time.' },
    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'Should I take collagen or hyaluronic acid for skin?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Both serve different but complementary functions. Collagen provides structural support — it is the scaffolding that maintains skin firmness and prevents sagging. Collagen production declines approximately 1% per year after age 20. Hyaluronic acid is a humectant that holds up to 1,000x its weight in water, providing skin hydration and plumpness. HA levels also decline with age. For comprehensive skin support, take both: collagen for structural integrity and elasticity, hyaluronic acid for hydration and plumpness. Products that combine both ingredients in a single gummy provide the most efficient approach.' },
    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'Can gummies replace my skincare routine?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'No. Skin gummies work from the inside out by supporting collagen synthesis, providing antioxidant protection, and maintaining hydration at the cellular level. Topical skincare works from the outside in by delivering active ingredients directly to the skin surface and upper layers. The most effective approach combines both: internal supplementation (collagen, vitamins C and E, hyaluronic acid) to support skin biology + external skincare (sunscreen, retinoids, moisturizers) to protect and treat the skin surface. Think of gummies as the foundation and topical products as the finishing layer.' },
    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'Are skin gummies safe for all skin types?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Yes. The vitamins, collagen, and hyaluronic acid in skin gummies are safe for all skin types — oily, dry, combination, and sensitive. Unlike topical products that can irritate sensitive skin or clog pores, oral supplements work through internal biological pathways and do not directly contact the skin surface. However, people with fish or shellfish allergies should check collagen sources (marine collagen is fish-derived). Those with autoimmune conditions affecting the skin should consult their dermatologist before supplementing. Pregnant women should verify ingredient safety with their healthcare provider.' },
    },
  ],
};
