    <h2 id="why-skin-gummies">The Science Behind Skin Gummies</h2>

    <p>Your skin is your body's largest organ, and its health depends on internal biological processes as much as external skincare. Collagen — the most abundant protein in your body — provides the structural scaffolding that keeps skin firm, elastic, and wrinkle-resistant. Collagen production declines approximately 1% per year after age 20, accelerating in women after menopause. By age 50, most people have lost 25-30% of their skin collagen. Supplementing collagen peptides from the inside supports the skin's structural foundation in a way that topical creams cannot reach.</p>

    <div class="key-stat">
      <span class="key-stat-num">1%</span>
      <p class="key-stat-txt">of skin collagen is lost per year after age 20. A systematic review of <strong>11 randomized controlled trials found that collagen peptide supplementation significantly improved skin elasticity, hydration, and wrinkle depth</strong> compared to placebo. Results were measurable at 8 weeks and continued improving through 24 weeks of daily use.</p>
    </div>

    <p>Beyond collagen, three additional nutrients are critical for skin health: vitamin C (essential cofactor for collagen synthesis — without it, collagen cannot be produced), hyaluronic acid (holds 1,000x its weight in water for deep hydration), and vitamin E (antioxidant that protects skin cells from UV-induced free radical damage). The best skin gummies combine these ingredients to support collagen production, hydration, and antioxidant defense simultaneously — addressing the three pillars of skin aging from the inside.</p>

    <div class="info-cards">
      <div class="info-card">
        <div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="sparkle" size={22} /></div>
        <strong>Collagen Peptides — Firmness</strong>
        <p>Hydrolyzed collagen peptides are absorbed in the intestine and distributed to the skin via the bloodstream. They stimulate fibroblasts to produce new collagen and elastin, improving skin firmness and reducing wrinkle depth. Verisol and Peptan are the most clinically studied collagen brands.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="droplet" size={22} /></div>
        <strong>Hyaluronic Acid — Hydration</strong>
        <p>HA is a glycosaminoglycan that holds up to 1,000x its weight in water. Oral HA supplementation (120-240mg daily) increases skin moisture content measurably within 6 weeks. It plumps skin from within, reducing the appearance of fine lines caused by dehydration.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="flask" size={22} /></div>
        <strong>Vitamin C — Collagen Synthesis</strong>
        <p>Vitamin C is an essential cofactor for prolyl hydroxylase and lysyl hydroxylase — the enzymes that stabilize the collagen triple helix structure. Without adequate vitamin C, collagen cannot be properly synthesized. It also brightens skin by inhibiting tyrosinase, the enzyme responsible for melanin production.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="info-card">
        <div class="info-card-ico"><Icon name="shield" size={22} /></div>
        <strong>Vitamin E — Antioxidant Shield</strong>
        <p>Vitamin E is a fat-soluble antioxidant that protects cell membranes from lipid peroxidation caused by UV radiation and environmental pollution. Working synergistically with vitamin C, it provides 4x the antioxidant protection of either vitamin alone.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="callout">
      <p>A landmark study published in <em>Skin Pharmacology and Physiology</em> found that <strong>2.5g of Verisol collagen peptides daily for 8 weeks reduced eye wrinkle volume by 20%</strong> and increased skin procollagen production by 65%. A follow-up study showed improvements continued through 12 weeks, with skin elasticity increasing by 15% compared to placebo.</p>
      <cite>Skin Pharmacology and Physiology — Oral Supplementation with Specific Bioactive Collagen Peptides</cite>
    </div>

